"n.甜瓜 【考】 apple : skin / melon : rind(苹果和苹果皮/甜瓜 和甜瓜皮) 【记】 mel(甜)+on→甜的东 西→甜瓜; 【同】 参考：watermelon(西 瓜) n. 甜瓜(具有坚硬的瓜皮和多汁的瓤) 【记】mel甜蜜, on－甜瓜 【参】watermelon(n 西瓜) 【类】apple: skin = melon: find苹果和苹果皮 = 甜瓜和甜瓜皮 【记】音：蜜嫩，吃着蜜嫩的；西瓜是watermelon；melt 融化 melon (n.)  late 14c., from Old French melon (13c.), from Medieval Latin melonem (nominative melo), from Latin melopeponem, a kind of pumpkin, from Greek melopepon ""gourd-apple"" (name for several kinds of gourds bearing sweet fruit), from melon ""apple"" (see malic) + pepon, a kind of gourd, probably noun use of pepon ""ripe"" (see pumpkin). In Greek, melon  was used in a generic way for all foreign fruits (compare similar use of apple). The Greek plural of ""melon"" was used from ancient times for ""a girl's breasts."""
